<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06072214 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06072214 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  INDIANA; COLLEGE; BASKETBALL; COACH; CONTROVERSY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  It's NCAA tournament time, and Bob Knight is primed for the postseason.;   The Indiana coach, whose notoriety for chair-throwing and Puerto Ricanpolice-bashing has often overshadowed his three national championship bannersand an Olympic gold medal, got under the skin of Illinois Coach Lou Henson onSunday.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  KNIGHT'S A 'BULLY,' ILLINI COACH SAYS  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     A confrontation after Indiana's 70-58 win prompted Henson to refer toKnight as a &quot;classic bully.&quot;;    Monday, Henson said the incident was justanother example of Knight's &quot;running roughshod over people.&quot;;    Illinoisassistant Jimmy Collins called the confrontation &quot;one of the worst I've seen.&quot;Illini junior Andy Kaufmann said Henson &quot;was plenty mad. People had to pullhim away.&quot;;    The fireworks began after Knight, laughing and waving to thecrowd, left the court with seven seconds to play.;    In the hall leading tothe locker rooms, Henson and Knight traded words in an exchange punctuatedwith profanity from Knight, witnesses told the News Gazette ofChampaign-Urbana and the Chicago Tribune.;    During his news conference,Knight launched into a sarcastic, 10-minute monologue on the plight ofIllinois basketball, which is under NCAA sanctions.;    &quot;I really thinkthere's an international conspiracy to get Illinois,&quot; Knight said.;    Hensonsaid he asked Knight to &quot;step outside.&quot;;    &quot;His entire life is based onintimidation,&quot; Henson said, &quot;but the big bully won't intimidate me.&quot;  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Champaign, Ill.  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910312  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  220  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday March 12, 199100072214,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>